		Comment <a href="#c_1713649604">21</a> by Teddy
		posted on 1/26/2006 at 9:48 PM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>I get the feeling that perhaps apples and oranges are in discussion here.  Database related topics should be included, but as they relate to ColdFusion.  We may be lost in the idea of providing syntax for 4-5 major databases and this seems arduous for those that focus on 1-2.  I am all for knowing how to use MS-SQl, MySQL and PL-SQL for a solution, but I think the integration parts should be more focused upon.</p><p>An example would be aliased columns in a CFQUERY tag.  MS-SQL supports many differents ways to create an alias for a record column, but natively inside the CFQUERY there is a more limited choice for Ad-hoc queries.</p><p>Select Foo AS 'Foo_Colum' or Select Foo 'Foo_Column'</p><p>The above examples are acceptable for MS-SQL, but will cause issues with versions of CF.  CF supports rather:</p><p>Select Foo AS Foo_Column</p><p>Foo_Column without single quotes.  I understand that this may be minor and Stored Procs is a better solution, but a SQL newbie may not understand why CF doen't understand the MS-SQl documentation of aliased columns.</p><p>I think the CF exceptions to DB manufacturers should be included, but a complete list of all possible notations in each of the 5 DB's standards for SQL should not be.</p></div>
	</div>
